Wall art for hotels, offices & hospitality

Custom printed wall art for commercial interiors, produced on demand with no minimum orders.

Prodigi provides custom wall art for hotels, offices, restaurants and commercial spaces. All products are printed in-house at facilities in the UK (Alton), EU (Venlo, Netherlands) and US (Charlotte, North Carolina), with no minimum order quantities and delivery to more than 170 countries worldwide.

Start your project View wall art products

What is commercial wall art?

Commercial wall art is custom printed artwork produced for business environments – from framed prints in hotel rooms to large-format canvas pieces in corporate reception areas.

Unlike traditional art procurement, which requires bulk ordering, long lead times and high upfront costs, Prodigi's print-on-demand wall art lets you order exactly what you need, when you need it. One piece or one thousand – there are no minimum order quantities at any tier.

Prodigi prints in-house at owned production facilities in the UK, EU and US, using water-based, eco-friendly inks on conservation-grade materials. Every product is delivered ready to hang.

Why choose Prodigi for commercial wall art?

🏭

In-house production

Printed at Prodigi's own facilities in Alton (UK), Venlo (Netherlands) and Charlotte (US). Not outsourced, not brokered – produced under Prodigi's direct quality control.

📦

No minimum orders

Order a single framed print for a boutique hotel room or 500 canvases for a corporate rollout. No minimums, ever, at any tier.

🎨

Fine Art Trade Guild certified

Prodigi is an approved Fine Art Trade Guild printer – the industry's quality benchmark for fine art reproduction and commercial printing.

🌍

Global fulfilment

Production in three continents means your order is printed closer to its destination. Faster delivery, lower shipping costs, reduced carbon footprint.

♻️

Sustainable materials

Conservation-grade, acid-free mounts. Water-based inks. Sustainably sourced wood frames. Ecocaps packaging eliminates single-use plastic.

⚡

Fast turnaround

Over 80% of custom products are ready for dispatch within 24–48 hours. Prodigi ships to more than 170 countries worldwide.

Wall art for every commercial interior

Hotels & hospitality

Create a distinctive guest experience with custom framed prints and canvas art tailored to your property's character. Prodigi's print-on-demand model means you can personalise art for individual rooms, lobbies and common areas without committing to bulk orders. Refresh seasonal displays or respond to refurbishment schedules on demand.

Offices & corporate spaces

Transform workspaces with brand-aligned wall art that reinforces company culture. From metal prints in reception areas to modular photo tiles in breakout spaces, Prodigi provides the flexibility to outfit a single office or roll out across multiple locations via the Print API.

Restaurants, bars & retail

Set the tone for your venue with high-gloss acrylic prints, wooden prints or classic box frames. Prodigi's 200+ customisable products mean you can match any design brief, and the extra-large format range handles statement pieces up to 100×50 inches.

How it works

1

Upload your artwork

Sign up free at dashboard.prodigi.com and upload your designs. Use the mockup generator to preview products before ordering.

2

Choose your products

Select from 200+ wall art products including framed prints, canvas, metal and acrylic. Sizes range from 4×6 inches to 100×50 inches.

3

Prodigi prints & ships

Your order is routed to the nearest Prodigi production facility – UK, EU or US – and printed in-house. Over 80% of orders dispatch within 24–48 hours, delivered to 170+ countries.

4

Scale with the API

For multi-location rollouts or ongoing programmes, integrate via the Print API or CSV importer for bulk ordering. No minimum order quantities apply at any volume.

Wall art products for commercial spaces

Framed prints

Classic, box and spacer frames in sustainably sourced wood. Conservation-grade mounts, delivered ready to hang.

Canvas prints

Hand-stretched or framed canvas, up to 52.5×68 inches. Gallery-quality Giclée printing on premium cotton-blend canvas.

Metal prints

Aluminium and dibond prints with floating mount hardware. Vibrant colours, scratch-resistant, ideal for high-traffic areas.

Acrylic prints

High-gloss perspex panels. Shatter-resistant and scratch-resistant, with vivid colour reproduction and a contemporary look.

Who is commercial wall art for?

Prodigi works with interior designers, hotel groups, office fit-out companies, restaurant chains, co-working spaces, healthcare facilities and retail brands. Whether you are sourcing art for a single project or managing an ongoing programme across multiple sites, Prodigi's platform scales to fit.

For businesses ordering at volume, Prodigi Pro offers a 10% discount on all products plus branded packaging inserts for a fully white-label experience.

Need help scoping a project? Contact the sales team at sales@prodigi.com or visit About Prodigi to learn more about the company.

Frequently asked questions

What is commercial wall art printing?

Commercial wall art printing is the production of custom artwork for business environments such as hotels, offices, restaurants and retail spaces. Prodigi offers over 200 wall art products – including framed prints, canvas, metal and acrylic – printed on demand at in-house facilities in the UK, EU and US, with no minimum order quantities.

How does print-on-demand wall art work for hotels?

Hotels upload artwork to the Prodigi platform, select products and sizes, and place orders as needed. Each piece is printed individually at the nearest Prodigi facility, so properties can customise art for specific rooms or refresh seasonal displays without holding inventory.

What is the minimum order quantity for commercial printing?

There is no minimum order quantity with Prodigi, at any tier. Clients can order a single framed print or thousands of pieces for a multi-site rollout. This applies to all 200+ products, from small prints to extra-large wall art up to 100×50 inches.

How long does production and delivery take?

Prodigi dispatches over 80% of custom wall art products within 24–48 hours. With production facilities in the UK (Alton), Netherlands (Venlo) and the US (Charlotte), orders are printed closer to their destination for faster delivery and lower shipping costs. Prodigi delivers to more than 170 countries.

What wall art products are suitable for high-traffic areas?

For high-traffic commercial spaces, Prodigi recommends metal prints (scratch-resistant aluminium with vibrant colours) and acrylic panels (shatter-resistant perspex). Both are durable, easy to clean and available in sizes up to 40×60 inches.

Can I order wall art for multiple office locations?

Prodigi supports multi-location ordering through the Print API for automated integration, the CSV importer for bulk uploads, or the manual order form for one-off orders. Each order ships directly to its destination address.

What quality certifications does Prodigi hold?

Prodigi is an approved Fine Art Trade Guild printer – the industry's recognised quality standard for fine art reproduction. All products use conservation-grade, acid-free mounts, water-based eco-friendly inks, and archival materials rated for over 200 years of display permanence.

How do I get started with commercial wall art from Prodigi?

Sign up free at dashboard.prodigi.com. There are no monthly fees – you pay only when orders go to production. Upload your artwork, use the mockup generator to preview products, and place your first order. For large projects, contact sales@prodigi.com.

Is Prodigi's packaging sustainable?

Prodigi uses Ecocaps – a proprietary sustainable packaging system made from 100% recycled materials. Ecocaps has eliminated over two million pieces of single-use plastic from Prodigi's supply chain. All packaging and materials are selected for minimal environmental impact.

Why choose Prodigi over traditional art suppliers?

Traditional art suppliers require bulk orders, long lead times and upfront deposits. Prodigi prints on demand with no minimums, dispatches 80%+ of orders within 24–48 hours, and charges per order with no deposits or monthly fees. Production at owned facilities in three countries ensures consistent quality and fast global delivery.

Ready to discuss your project?

Contact the Prodigi sales team to scope your commercial wall art requirements.
